If two or 3 USB devices are used, in order that they will be named properly, insert
them to different ports one by one until two conditions are met:

1.
  ttyACM0 belongs to device showing mm:hh
  ttyACM1 belongs to device showing :ss
  ttyACM2 belongs to gps device

2.
  in the output of the following command bus number for ttyACM0 is the smallest
  and for ttyACM2 is the greatest

    ls -l /sys/class/tty/ttyACM*

NOTE: on raspberry pi the sequence of ports is:

+---+ +---+
| A | | C |
+---+ +---+
+---+ +---+
| B | | D |
+---+ +---+

==========================================================

Connect programmator as:

( ) (G) (O) (.) ( ) ( ) ( ) ( ) (B) (G) (V) (.)

(G) = Gray
(O) = Orange
(B) = Brown
(V) = Violet
( ) = no pin
(.) = unused pin

-------------------------

In ConnectBot add entry to show/hide seconds (followed by return):

    if [ -e /tmp/time.no-seconds ]; then clock seconds; else clock no-seconds; fi; exit

and enable "close when connection disappears" in the entry properties

---------------------

/usr/sbin/ntpd.hotplug-helper is running as daemon (its contents are below).
NOTE: installing ntpd deletes /usr/sbin/ntpd, so /etc/init.d/sysntpd just becomes no-op, thus it never calls /usr/sbin//usr/sbin/ntpd.hotplug, thus '/sbin/hotplug-call ntp' is called only by /usr/sbin/ntpd.hotplug-helper
Modify it as follows:

Before the line

		ACTION="stratum" /sbin/hotplug-call ntp

we add:

		[ -f /var/state/dnsmasqsec ] || clock no-blink # time becomes valid; see rc.local

Before the line

		SLEEPTIME=660

we add:

		if [ -f /var/state/dnsmasqsec ]; then
			[ -e /tmp/time.blink ] && clock no-blink
		fi

After the line

		SLEEPTIME=660

we add:

	else
		if [ -f /var/state/dnsmasqsec ]; then
			[ -e /tmp/time.blink ] || clock blink
		fi
		SLEEPTIME=10

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#!/bin/sh

SLEEPTIME=10

while true
do
	STATUS="$(/usr/sbin/ntpq -c 'rv 0 stratum'|awk -F '=' '{ print $2 }')"

	if [[ -n "$STATUS" && "$STATUS" -lt "16" ]]
	then
		ACTION="stratum" /sbin/hotplug-call ntp
		SLEEPTIME=660
	fi
	sleep $SLEEPTIME
done
